San Jose, Costa Rica. Thursday 8 July, 1999
Red Alert
------------
The Minister of Health, Rogelio Pardo Evans, declared a red alert in Limon
yesterday, due to the epidemic of dengue which affected this province.
According to official records, yesterday alone there were 12 new suspect
cases of classic dengue.
On Tuesday there were 47 cases of the disease [dengue fever, none of
which were of the hemorrhagic type, considered to be the most dangerous.
In total there have been 112 cases of dengue -- principally in the city of
Limon -- since the past 3 July, when the epidemic was noted.
Up through the present there were six cases of dengue hemorrhagic reported,
two of which are qualified as severe, although those affected are out of
danger. The declaration of emergency is for an indefinite period of time
and obliges the provincial governmental institutions to help in the control
of the epidemic, spread by the mosquito _Aedes aegypti_.
---------------------
